UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387887900794
AB  - This paper investigates empirically the issue of a fixed versus a flexible exchange currency regime for a small economy: The West African Monetary Union. The econometric analysis implements a Mundellian trade-off between economic development and monetary stability which measures the main cost and benefit of the various exchange currency regimes examined. The empirical results indicate that the fixed trade-weighted basket peg is optimal by the Tower and Willet criterion and that it meets some of Kenen's criteria for an efficient exchange currency regime.
