AB  - Eaton and Gersovitz's model of borrowing with default risk was re-estimated using data from 1977 and 1981. The results of the re-estimation indicated that the developing countries were less credit constrained in the late seventies/early eighties than in the early dseventies. However, the model did not describe the later sample period as well as the earlier sample period. One reason for the reduced explanatory power of their model is that the model does not incorporate many of the changes that occured in the world economy after 1974 and does not reflect the current structure of indebtedness of the developing countries.
